<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                        Ambassador in China (
                        Stuart
                    )</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1948v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d8</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">8</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00" n="8" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.93/1–2948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-30T13:00:00-05:00">January 30, 1948—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>153. Third paragraph of your number 181 January 29<note n="30" xml:id="d8fn30">
                        <hi rend="italic">Post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_464">p. 464</ref>.</note>
                    contains expression “unless effective military assistance is forthcoming”. Just
                    what do you mean by the word “effective”.</p>
                <pb facs="0019" n="9" xml:id="pg_9"/>
                <p>Are you referring to material, or to leadership, or to advice, or to wholesale
                    removal of incompetent or venal commanders, or to American troops, or to
                    what?</p>
                <p>Are you considering long-range result of charge of United States acceptance of
                    responsibility for a military campaign with its inevitable international perils
                    and probable tremendous demands of one kind or another?</p>
                <p>I understand the proposals of your no. 181 regarding civilian matters but I am
                    not clear as to military. Please give me your own personal and individual
                    reaction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
